			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>Unconscious Injured Diver
Regardless of whether there is a spinal injury suspected, an unconscious diver must be removed from the exhibit to perform CPR &amp; First Aid
If diver is underwater
Bring diver to the surface
Control ascent (drop weights, inflate BCD)
Manage open airway
Establish positive buoyancy at the surface
Remove injured diver’s equipment
Extricate the diver in the most expedient manner
Care for conditions found (CPR, first aid)</text>
		</slide>
